  "blocks": [
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 1,
      "text": "Cam Chain Removal and Installation"
    },
    {
      "type": "attention",
      "items": [
        "Keep magnetized objects away from the cam chain.",
        "When removing the cam chain, the No. 1 piston must be aligned with the upper dead center of the exhaust."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "1. Right side front wheel removal",
      "refs": [
        {
          "id": "R000659",
          "label": "Right side front wheel removal",
          "resolved": true
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "2. Front bumper removal",
      "refs": [
        {
          "id": "R000814",
          "label": "Front bumper removal",
          "resolved": true
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "3. Front upper grille removal",
      "refs": [
        {
          "id": "R000842",
          "label": "Front upper grille removal",
          "resolved": true
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "4. Right side front splash guard removal",
      "refs": [
        {
          "id": "R000849",
          "label": "Right side front splash guard removal",
          "resolved": true
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "5. A.C. generator belt removal",
      "refs": [
        {
          "id": "R000351",
          "label": "A.C. generator belt removal",
          "resolved": true
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "6. A.C. generator stay removal"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "369_5.0_jpn_11582766_5.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "7. Water pump Belt removal",
      "refs": [
        {
          "id": "R000433",
          "label": "Water pump Belt removal",
          "resolved": true
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "8. Crankshaft Pulley TDC mark Alignment"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "369_5.0_jpn_11582767_5.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Rotate the crankshaft pulley in a clockwise direction to align the alignment mark (A) with the TDC mark (white marking) (B)."
    },
    {
      "type": "attention",
      "items": [
        "Confirmation shall be made from the specified viewing direction (C)."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "9. Exhaust top dead center Positioning"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "369_5.0_jpn_11582768_5.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Remove the cylinder head cover.",
      "refs": [
        {
          "id": "R000371",
          "label": "Remove the cylinder head cover.",
          "resolved": true
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "2",
      "text": "Align the TDC mark (A) on the VTC actuator and exhaust camshaft sprocket with the top of the cylinder head, with the TDC marks (A) facing outward. This is the position at which the No. 1 piston is at the top dead center of the exhaust."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "10. Crankshaft pulley removal",
      "refs": [
        {
          "id": "R000368",
          "label": "Crankshaft pulley removal",
          "resolved": true
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "11. Remove side engine mount assembly.",
      "refs": [
        {
          "id": "R000357",
          "label": "Remove side engine mount assembly.",
          "resolved": true
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "12. リレー ボックス ステイ 取外し"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "369_5.0_jpn_11582769_5.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Disconnect the coupler (A). Remove the harness clamp (B). Remove the A/C pipe clamp (C). Remove the relay box stay (D)."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "13. Engine Wire Harness Stay Removal"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "369_5.0_jpn_11582770_5.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "14. Chain case mounting bolt removal"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "369_5.0_jpn_11582771_5.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "15. Chain case removal"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "369_5.0_jpn_11582772_5.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "16. Cam chain tensioner removal"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "369_5.0_jpn_11582773_5.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Temporarily tighten the crankshaft pulley."
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "369_5.0_jpn_11582774_5.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "3",
      "text": "Insert a pin (A) with an outside diameter of 1.2 mm where the hole in the lock and the hole in the cam chain tensioner align, and rotate the crankshaft clockwise to secure the pin."
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "369_5.0_jpn_11582775_5.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "4",
      "text": "Remove the cam chain tensioner."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "17. Cam Chain Guide B Removal"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "369_5.0_jpn_11582776_5.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "18. Cam Chain Guide/Cam Chain Tensioner Arm Removal"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "369_5.0_jpn_11582777_5.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Remove the cam chain guide (A) and cam chain tensioner arm (B)."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "19. Cam chain removal"
    },
    {
      "type": "attention",
      "items": [
        "Keep magnetized objects away from the cam chain.",
        "When installing the cam chain, the No. 1 piston must be aligned with the upper dead center of the exhaust."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "1. Cam Chain Mounting"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "369_5.0_jpn_11582778_5.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Align the TDC mark (A) on the crankshaft sprocket with the alignment mark (B) on the oil pump."
    },
    {
      "type": "attention",
      "items": [
        "Install the key (C) with care, paying attention to its orientation."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "369_5.0_jpn_11582779_5.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "2",
      "text": "Align the TDC marks (A) on the VTC actuator and exhaust camshaft sprocket with each other on the outside and with the upper end surface of the cylinder head. This is the position at which the No. 1 piston is at the top dead center of the exhaust."
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "369_5.0_jpn_11582780_5.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "3",
      "text": "Align the punch mark (A) on the VTC actuator and exhaust camshaft sprocket with the collar plate (B) on the cam chain and engage the cam chain."
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "369_5.0_jpn_11582781_5.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "4",
      "text": "Align the cam chain collar plate (A) with the TDC mark (punch mark) (B) on the crankshaft sprocket and engage the cam chain."
    },
    {
      "type": "attention",
      "items": [
        "Align the two color plates so that the punch mark is between the two color plates.",
        "After installing the cam chain, be sure to check that the crankshaft sprocket and camshaft sprocket are aligned with the upper dead center of the No. 1 piston exhaust."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "2. Cam Chain Guide/Cam Chain Tensioner Arm Mounting"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "369_5.0_jpn_11582782_5.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Install the cam chain guide (A) and cam chain tensioner arm (B)."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "3. Cam Chain Guide B Mounting"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "369_5.0_jpn_11582783_5.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "4. Cam Chain Tensioner Installation"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "369_5.0_jpn_11582784_5.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "To replace the cam chain, remove the pin (B) from the cam chain tensioner (C) while holding the rod (A) so that it will not fly out, turn the plate (D) counterclockwise to unlock it, and push the rod to the position (G) where the cam (E) can be set at the end of the rack (F). Insert the 1.2 mm diameter pin into the hole (H)."
    },
    {
      "type": "attention",
      "items": [
        "Set the chain tensioner according to the procedure, as the tensioner may be damaged."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "369_5.0_jpn_11582785_5.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "2",
      "text": "Install the cam chain tensioner."
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "369_5.0_jpn_11582786_5.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "3",
      "text": "Remove the pin (A) from the cam chain tensioner."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "5. Pulley end Crankshaft oil seal Inspect"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Inspect the pulley end crankshaft oil seal, Replace if necessary.",
      "refs": [
        {
          "id": "R000393",
          "label": "Replace if necessary.",
          "resolved": true
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "6. Chain case mounting"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "369_5.0_jpn_11582787_5.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Remove old fluid packings, oil, and dirt from oil pan, cylinder block, cylinder head, chain case, bolts, and bolt holes."
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "2",
      "text": "Apply Honda Genuine Fluid Packing 1216E to the cylinder head and cylinder block contact surfaces of the chain case."
    },
    {
      "type": "attention",
      "items": [
        "Apply liquid packing with a wire diameter of about 2.5 mm along the dashed line (A).",
        "The mating surface (B) of the cylinder head and cylinder block shall be coated with a 11 mm wide, 2.5 mm wire diameter liquid packing."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "369_5.0_jpn_11582788_5.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "3",
      "text": "Apply Honda Genuine Fluid Packing 1216E to the chain case oil pan contact surface."
    },
    {
      "type": "attention",
      "items": [
        "Apply liquid packing with a wire diameter of about 2.5 mm along the dashed line (A).",
        "A liquid packing with a wire diameter of about 6 mm shall be applied to the shaded area (B)."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "369_5.0_jpn_11582789_5.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "4",
      "text": "Insert the chain case."
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "369_5.0_jpn_11582790_5.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "5",
      "text": "Align the crankshaft pulley side of the chain case (A) and oil pan (B) before installing the chain case into the cylinder block (C)."
    },
    {
      "type": "attention",
      "items": [
        "If the liquid packing is left on for more than 4 minutes after application, do not install it as it is. Remove the packing once and reapply.",
        "Oil should be injected at least 30 minutes after installation.",
        "Do not touch the liquid packing-applied surface.",
        "The engine should be started at least 3 hours after installation.",
        "Do not slide the chain case during installation, as this will cause the liquid packing to become uneven, resulting in oil leaks, etc.",
        "Wipe off any fluid packing that protrudes from the crankshaft pulley side."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "369_5.0_jpn_11582791_5.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "6",
      "text": "Tighten the chain case mounting bolts."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "7. Engine Wire Harness Stay Installation"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "369_5.0_jpn_11582792_5.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "8. Relay Box/Relay Box Stay Mounting"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "369_5.0_jpn_11582793_5.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Install relay box stay (A). Install the harness clamp (B). Install A/C pipe clamp (C). Connect the coupler (D)."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "9. Crankshaft pulley Installation",
      "refs": [
        {
          "id": "R000368",
          "label": "Crankshaft pulley Installation",
          "resolved": true
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "10. Side engine mount assembly."
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "369_5.0_jpn_11582794_5.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Tighten the new side engine mount mounting bolts (A). Temporarily tighten the new side engine mount bracket mounting nut (B) and loosen the side engine mount bracket mounting bolt (C). Install the ground cable (D). Perform the side engine mount tightening procedure.",
      "refs": [
        {
          "id": "R000357",
          "label": "Perform the side engine mount tightening procedure.",
          "resolved": true
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "attention",
      "items": [
        "When the side engine mount assembly is removed and installed, the transmission mount and torque rod must be tightened in the correct sequence."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "11. A/C Pipe Fixed"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "369_5.0_jpn_11582795_5.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Attach A/C pipe to clamp (A). Install the harness clamp (B) on the A/C compressor. Install the A/C pipe clamp bolt (C)."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "12. Cylinder Head Cover Installation",
      "refs": [
        {
          "id": "R000371",
          "label": "Cylinder Head Cover Installation",
          "resolved": true
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "13. Water Pump Belt Installation",
      "refs": [
        {
          "id": "R000433",
          "label": "Water Pump Belt Installation",
          "resolved": true
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "14. A.C. Generator Stay Installation"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "369_5.0_jpn_11582796_5.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "15. A.C. generator Belt installation",
      "refs": [
        {
          "id": "R000351",
          "label": "A.C. generator Belt installation",
          "resolved": true
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
